republican george bush on tuesday called for a federal law 
banning discrimination against aids sufferers to lay to rest some 
fears democrat michael dukakis endorsed spending 3 billion on 
new housing programs 
meanwhile gop sources said new jersey gov thomas kean had been 
tapped as the keynote speaker for the republican convention in new 
orleans in august word filtered out the day after the democrats 
announced that texas state treasurer ann richards would give the 
opening speech at their convention 
dukakis just three weeks away from the democratic national 
convention in atlanta suggested there was no point in paying 
attention to public speculation about who might be on his list for 
the vice presidential nomination 
theres only one guy who knows whats going on and thats the 
guy youre looking at the massachusetts governor told reporters 
in boston 
jesse jackson who is still contesting the democratic 
presidential nomination as well as saying he deserves consideration 
for the no 2 spot faced a snarled schedule as plane troubles 
forced cancellation of a texas speech 
vice president bush campaigning in californias silicon valley 
came out strongly in favor of the report of president reagans 
commission on aids calling it a landmark analysis 
bush the certain gop nominee praised the report for 
recognizing the need for patient notification and widespread 
testing as a means to limit the spread of aids such programs would 
be ineffective without being coupled with strict confidentiality 
and antidiscrimination provisions 
on air force two on the way to california from washington bush 
said that means he supports a federal law barring discrimination 
against aids sufferers a key provision of the report on which 
reagan has yet to take a position 
i think it is needed bush said i think it is important 
to do a lot to lay to rest some of the fears there is a lot of 
misunderstanding 
i would hate if a kid of mine got a blood transfusion if my 
grandson had aids and the community discriminated against that 
child innocent child particularly when the report concludes 
aids is not cant be transmitted in ways that some had feared 
bush said 
dukakis responded to the report last week saying in a statement 
issued friday we join the commission in its call for tougher 
antidiscrimination and confidentiality measures we support their 
call for expanded education and research programs and innovative 
approaches to providing care 
in his response dukakis urged reagan to act on the commissions 
recommendations before leaving office 
we must come together in this time of crisis and demonstrate 
the true american character of compassion and caring for our fellow 
human beings living with aids dukakis said in the statement 
dukakis tried to keep the focus on issues tuesday speaking to a 
housing forum in boston and then touring a site where more than a 
dozen homes have been sold to low and moderateincome people 
through a state program offering subsidized mortgages 
i dont see how we can talk about a bright economic future for 
america if it doesnt include decent and affordable housing for all 
our citizens dukakis said in a speech to the housing forum 
he promised if elected to provide 3 billion to carry out a 
program that would be established under legislation sponsored by 
sen alan cranston of california cranston joined dukakis for the 
event 
dukakis blamed what he said was a lack of affordable housing on 
a 90 percent cut in federal spending on housing by the reagan 
administration he brushed aside questions about bushs stand on 
housing saying i dont know that he has a policy 
reporters pressed dukakis on how the process of picking a 
running mate is going especially since he is flying to washington 
on wednesday to meet with many democratic senators 
some of them may be possibilities dukakis said 
the massachusetts governor answered with a flat no when 
asked if sen bob graham of florida had been ruled out he refused 
to answer directly about sen sam nunn of georgia saying only that 
he would talk with nunn on wednesday 
nunn has said he doesnt want to be considered 
republicans kept up their fire on dukakis with former united 
nations ambassador jeane kirkpatrick saying he doesnt have the 
experience that bush does 
i dont know michael dukakis personally but we all know that 
he has had no opportunity in his life to really devote himself to 
foreign affairs he has been concerned above all with local and 
state affairs and george bush has been concerned with the world 
she told reporters in washington 
meanwhile the bush campaign put out new materials on the 
massachusetts prison furlough program that dukakis has defended and 
bush has criticized the materials said there had been a 
dangerous increase in the furlough program in the last three 
years including a doubling of furloughs for prisoners convicted of 
drug offenses 
leslie dach dukakis communications director responded to the 
statement saying the bush campaign continues to try and erect a 
smoke screen around george bushs leadership of a failed war 
against drugs michael dukakis has run a criminal justice system 
thats increased convictions for drug offenses 500 percent in five 
years 
democrat jesse jackson speaking tuesday night to a convention 
of operation push the chicagobased civil rights group he founded 
said federal programs to help minority businesses should be 
expanded 
jackson told the group meeting in rosemont ill that minority 
businesses should receive 10 percent of all contracts with federal 
agencies 
minority business enterprise and womens business enterprise 
require a national focus and priority commitments in order that 
these key areas of our economy can reach their fullest potential 
jackson said the setaside program needs improvement and 
expansion not termination 
meanwhile richards the democrats choice for keynote speaker 
got some advice from the 1984 keynoter new york gov mario cuomo 
i said the speech must be yours cuomo said he told 
richards you should write it and then you should read it to the 
people in your office not the pros forget the pros do it 
with your secretary with your accountants with your elevator 
operators 
get the ordinary audience as much of an ordinary audience as 
you can and you will learn extraordinary things cuomo said he 
told richards 
