patrick kennedy the 20yearold son of 
sen edward m kennedy said tuesday he is running for the rhode 
island state house of representatives 
there are no limits to my interest in public service the 
providence college student said as he announced he was seeking a 
twoyear legislative term the democratic primary is sept 14 
kennedy the younger son of the massachusetts senator will be 
challenging a fiveterm incumbent rep john skeffington jr for 
the 9th district democratic nomination skeffington 50 filed his 
candidacy papers tuesday while kennedy said he would do so 
wednesday 
the contest between the two men heated up weeks ago when 
skeffington expressed disappointment that kennedy wanted to run 
against him 
i cant believe the kennedys are going to try to knock out a 
true democrat he said then 
but kennedy felt no qualms about his action of course hes 
getting challenged this is what democracy is all about he said 
its not the kennedys coming in to the state its patrick 
kennedy kennedy said 
this is where ive made my home and this is where i plan to 
live he said 
skeffington a funeral director has deep family roots in 
providences mount pleasant section and is wellliked by the 
democratic heirarchy at the statehouse in 1986 however he won 
renomination by only 185 votes against a 22yearold political 
newcomer 
the ethnic bluecollar neighborhood has been strongly 
democratic for decades and winning the democratic primary has 
virtually guaranteed the winning seat 
kennedy said his campaign will focus on issues of crime 
affordable health care and affordable housing 
without directly attacking his rival kennedy said to be a 
good state representative doesnt just mean lounging around its 
active listening of the peoples concerns 
kennedy is president of the providence college democrats and was 
elected in a march primary as a national convention delegate he is 
pledged to democratic presidential frontrunner michael s dukakis 
in april young kennedy underwent surgery for the removal of a 
noncancerous tumor that had been pressing against his spine 
