the colossal tent of the roaring lions 
ponderous pachyderms cavorting clowns and doers of deathdefying 
deeds is 5000 miles from home about to dazzle the mysterious east 
ringling brothers and barnum and bailey circus known here as 
ringuringu burathazu ando bahnamu ando bairee sahkasu is 
making its first appearance abroad 15 weeks in japan beginning 
friday in the red and yellow big top 
hundreds of animals and people are assembled on the outskirts of 
this northern city getting ready to astound the japanese 
i think theyll get a kick out of it said kenneth feld who 
produces the wonders of the famous circus its so visual its 
not a language thing that they have to understand 
but ringling brothers is taking no chances about language 
singing ringmaster dinny mcguire besides riding a galumphing 
elephant in the opening number also must deliver his lines in 
japanese 
amazing elephants strange clowns he called out in japanese 
from his unsteady perch during a rehearsal beautiful showgirls 
gathered from all over the world to present to you the wonders of 
the circus 
ships planes and 100 tractortrailer trucks delivered mcguire 
25 clowns a 14piece band 16 elephants 14 lions and assorted 
horses ponies camels llamas humans and equipment for the 
threering assault on the the japanese imagination 
customs officials poked through scores of containers marked as 
containing costumes shoes nuts and bolts but an item labeled 
glue guns stopped them said mike fauls the general manager 
it was a big brouhaha he said it took several meetings 
and many days in the future well call them glue machines 
haphazard roads and numerous regulations mean the circus will do 
most of its moving by sea from the northern island of hokkaido to 
its second stop in tokyo later this summer and then on to osaka 
the 11day pacific crossing already has taken its toll on the 
elephants which range from babies to 14000pound adults feld 
said some had lost 800 pounds and were bleary when two shinto 
priests threw confetti on them at a welcoming ceremony june 13 
he said it cost about 10 million to create the overseas troupe 
as a supplement to ringlings two permanent american tours feld 
hopes to pack in the japanese even at ticket prices equivalent to 
about 40 a head and is planning a 25week tour for next year 
the japanese people have a lot of money and they work five 
days a week now instead of six he said theres no reason we 
cant have a circus in japan six months of the year 
what i hope is to build a tradition so i can come back every 
year every year japanese kids will look forward to the ringling 
bros and barnum and bailey circus 
feld doesnt seem bothered that the soviet unions bolshoi 
circus with a shorter name and decades of appearances here is 
more famous in japan and is playing at the same time 
hey he said with a shrug when youre the greatest show 
on earth 
