<TEXT>
grave robbers have broken into and plundered more 
than 1400 ancient tombs around the ancient chinese capital of 
luoyang an official newspaper said today 
the china daily said tomb robbing is rampant around the central 
china city capital of several dynasties that date back 3500 
years and that most of the thieves are peasants who sell their 
booty to relics smugglers 
it said there is a saying among villagers unearth ancient 
tombs to get rich and become a millionaire overnight 
in one county near luoyang 1000 people from 100 villages are 
involved in tomb robbing many emboldened by light punishment for 
those caught are now banding together to dig up graves during the 
daytime the report said 
although the government last year announced a crackdown on 
illegal excavating and relics smuggling offenders are generally 
only fined and released according to the report 
it also said that in a twomonth period last summer 500 people 
in the luoyang area were discovered smuggling relics some 
government officials were also found to be involved in smuggling 
operations the daily said 
