<TEXT>
members of the womans national democratic 
club will vote wednesday on allowing its 85 male members to vote or 
hold office and the clubs president says the governing board has 
recommended approval 
the 66yearold club was the target monday of a discrimination 
complaint filed by george washington university law professor john 
f banzhaf iii 
his complaint was filed with the district of columbias office 
of human rights to encourage the vote to give the clubs male 
members the same status in the organization as its 1815 women 
members banzhaf said 
