the nations roman catholic bishops 
decided to revamp their stand on fighting aids to quell a division 
within the church but stopped short of condemning a paper that 
tolerates teaching about condoms 
the national conference of catholic bishops concluded monday by 
unanimously approving a decision to appoint a committee to draft a 
new aids paper the updated document would be drawn in closer 
consultation with the vatican and acceptable to the entire 
conference church leaders said after a closed session at st 
johns university 
the division among ourselves the teachers is reflected among 
the people said a statement released by cardinal joseph 
bernardin of chicago who made the motion for the new paper we 
cannot allow it to continue festering our unity must be restored 
so we can get on with our business 
the many faces of aids a gospel approach was approved by 
the conferences administrative board and released last december 
but stirred controversy with the portion about condoms 
while stressing abstinence from sex outside marriage and 
fidelity within marriage the statement noted that many in society 
