high posted the previous day while stock prices on the tokyo 
exchange closed slightly lower after rebounding from heavy 
earlymorning losses 
the dollar opened the days trading at 13048 yen down a strong 
122 yen from mondays close of 13170 it moved mainly between a 
low of 13038 and a high of 13125 before finishing the day at 
13095 yen 
king ogino a dealer at goldman sachs said the dollars loss 
against the yen was driven by a comment from finance minister 
kiichi miyazawa who during a regular press conference dismissed 
recent currency changes as ordinary fluctuations the minister said 
the central bank would step into the market if necessary 
ogino said the statement led to depressed dollarselling at 
the 1308013090yen level and further profittaking sent the 
currency to about 13085 yen before it rebounded slightly 
todays loss snapped the dollars sixday winning streak during 
which the currency rose by a total of 482 yen mondays close of 
13170 yen was the highest finish for the dollar since dec 10 
when it closed at 13218 yen the next day the currency tumbled to 
12875 yen 
ogino said the mood on the foreign exchange market for the rest 
of the week would be dictated by movements of the central bank 
on the tokyo stock exchange meanwhile the nikkei stock average 
of 225 selected issues a 12120point loser monday regained lost 
ground following heavy morning losses but it still ended the day 
