editor of a small newspaper serving the black community was 
indicted on a charge of criminal libel for a column criticizing two 
politicians 
free speech means nothing if someone can go to jail for 
criticizing the government said steven bates chairman of south 
carolinas chapter of the american civil liberties union 
the aclu said it will petition for dismissal of the charges 
announced monday against jim fitt editor of the voice a 
williamsburg county weekly with a circulation of 2300 
state rep bj gordon who is black and state sen frank 
mcgill who is white brought the charges in response to a may 17 
column in which fitts urged voters to reject the politicians in the 
june primary and accused them of stealing 
representatives of reporters groups called the indictment a 
step backwards 
im really appalled said jane kirtley executive director 
