the michigan house elections committee 
voted unanimously tuesday in favor of reinstating a presidential 
primary election in 1992 
under the senatepassed bill which now goes to the full house 
voters would have to declare in advance whether they wanted to vote 
on the republican or democratic side 
the provision was added by lawmakers to meet the democratic 
national committee rules which dont recognize results of open 
primaries allowing members of each party to cross over and vote 
for another partys candidate 
in michigan the 1976 primary marked the last time that both 
major parties participated in the open primary the republicans had 
a primary in 1980 but opted for a multitiered convention system in 
the past two elections 
since 1980 the democrats have held caucuses every four years 
leaders of both parties have supported the return to a primary 
