several republican senators filed a bill 
tuesday to elevate the environmental protection agency to cabinet 
status saying the legislation was meant as a signal to the next 
administration that the environment should get more attention 
we want environmental protection to receive a higher priority 
than it has in the past said the author of the bill sen david 
durenberger rminn 
the bill would not change the duties or offices of the 
governments largest regulatory agency but would upgrade it to the 
department of environmental protection headed by a secretary 
the senators conceded that they had little hope of quick 
passage but said the bill was intended to prod presidential 
candidates into dealing with environmental issues 
i very much want george bush and michael dukakis to address 
environmental issues in their campaigns putting this issue before 
them will very much encourage that debate said sen john heinz 
rpa another sponsor 
