inmates from a turkish prison in march put austria on alert because 
of the possibility some might head for this country he said 
interpol the international police agency advised austrian 
officials of the escape 
mehmet ali agca now serving life in prison shot and seriously 
wounded the pope in may 1981 in st peters square in rome agca 
belonged to a rightwing turkish terrorist group called the gray 
wolves 
