the strategic defense initiative or star wars sources said 
administration critics have argued that such tests would violate 
the abm pact and reagan so far has refrained from implementing a 
socalled broad interpretation of the treaty which would allow 
more extensive testing 
the soviets have said they will not sign a strategic arms 
reduction treaty unless the united states agrees to abide by the 
abm pact for another 10 years 
for the past two years congress has barred the executive branch 
from spending any money on sdi tests that would violate the 
traditional or narrow interpretation of the abm pact 
