in his latest outing benji survives a shipwreck off the oregon 
coast and is on his way to a reunion with owner frank innes when he 
stumbles upon a litter of orphaned cougar cubs for the rest of the 
films 89 minutes benji struggles against rugged terrain and an 
assortment of human and animal villains to find the cubs shelter 
and a new mother 
director joe camp elicits a truly amazing performance from 
benji his expressive eyes registering whatever emotion the plot 
calls for whether it be fear or slyness or tenderness in one 
startling scene he brilliantly portrays a canine in conflict as 
