the senate on tuesday agreed to exempt 
businesses affected by the farm belt drought from legislation to 
make employers provide 60 days advance notice of large layoffs and 
plant closings 
the amendment by senate minority leader bob dole rkan was 
approved unanimously after farm state lawmakers said they have been 
told by bakeries flour mills and meatpacking poultry egg 
ethanol and farm equipment plants they anticipate future layoffs 
resulting from the drought currently afflicting much of the country 
